<HEADLINE>
POLICE BUST THEFT RING SPECIALIZING IN STEALING FASHION GOODS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taichung,  March 7 (CNA) 03/07/07  18:01:38 (By Han Nai-kuo)
</P>
<P>
Police have busted a theft ring that has broken into more than 10
boutiques in central and southern Taiwan since July last year and
has stolen NT$50 million- worth of name-brand fashion goods, a
spokesman for the Criminal Investigation Bureau announced
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the spokesman, a special task force was formed in
January to investigate a series of thefts in central and southern
Taiwan in which stores selling expensive fashion items, including
Louis Vuitton's flagship store in Taichung, suffered heavy
losses.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that a day earlier, task force agents raided
six locations in the cities of Kaohsiung and Tainan and the
counties of Kaohsiung and Changhua, arresting four members of the
ring identified as Huang Hsiung-chang, Kung Chao- hai, Lin Kuo-yu
and Liao Yu-li.
</P>
<P>
Police were still after another  member  of the ring, Tu Ching-
tsung, who jumped from a second floor window and escaped.
</P>
<P>
The task force also seized a wide variety of stolen fashion
goods, as well as tools believed to have been used for the break-
ins.
</P>
<P>
"We are trying to locate the owners of the goods and find out how
the thieves disposed of the rest of their loot," the spokesman
said.
</P>
